reviews.review_text: Fire Reprise? I had a great time at this run of shows.  I have not been able to get a copy of the first night until now.  The sound of the band during this run was not as heavy as the rest of 91'.  I think Vince really came into his own during the run with the band building momentum each night.  I really like the Cold Rain and TLEO from the first set and the Scarlet instrumental is excellent.  The Fire falls a bit short and doesnt end with the usual Scarlet ending also the band tries to go into Women are smarter but Bobby moves into LL Rain.  Near the end of the Terrapin jam, Phil plays the riff for Fire but noone bits.  Overall a nice show.

I was there, Rainy day outside, Cold Rain and Snow opener... I remember this show. Bought tickets with two of my buddies from highschool in the parking lot from Oaktown scalpers. Walked in late, about halfway through Cold Rain and Snow.
Played Loose Lucy, which my buddy Dave said they always played when he saw them. Sure enough they did.
I had been to the stellar halloween 91 shows earlier this year, so this show didn't compare in my opinion. Although, a good clean, standard dead performance. Good times. Let them roll...

Thymer

Was Havin a High Time,Livin' the Good Life I so remember this run. Was my first time in Oakland. I got to the lot and parked, the weather was crappy and I was dreading walking the lot lookin' for my ticket.I walked about 2 cars away, and a guy walked up to me, gave me a hug, and handed me a ticket, said Merry Christmas sister! Enjoy the show! I hadn't even started to look and there it was in my hand! I was so stoked!! Went in and when the show started I went up to the stage, Jerry's side. There were seats that had one of those velvet ropes sectioning it off from the steps, vips! I turned to walk away and someone grabbed my hand and told me to sit down there... Jerry must have known those people in that section, because he kept lookin over and grinnin'. Didn't even bother to look for my crew, because I felt like I was where I was meant to be. I have to say, one of my best Dead experiences to date.. Still lookin for the goose bumps the boys used to give me.. Man I wouldn't trade those days for anything in the world! Thank you Jerry !
